            <scopecontent id="aspace_01681fbc13c2a3f4cf718ff6c8973dad">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This accession comprises ledgers, farm recoeds, and family papers documenting the Selden family's farm life in Lyme, Connecticut. The ledgers, 1787-1884, were maintained by Richard Ely Selden and record purchases and payments for goods and services and logs of employee's activities and pay. Transactions include business dealings for timber, grass, hay, fish, livestock, and produce. The ledgers primarily document the farm's business, but they also record births and deaths, marriages performed by Selden, poems, and other personal matters. The farm records, 1787-1845, comprise manuscript material pertaining to the farm's business operations. The family papers, 1812-1868, comprise clippings, writings, and poetry pertaining to the Selden family.</p>
            </scopecontent>
